{
  "stem": "11744.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the German had snipers on all the roofs in Paris, and a lot of them-- there had been a lot of losses.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It had been very tough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went to the-- I went to the 50th anniversary of the liberation of Paris last year.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we re-did the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, the whole liberation of Paris took place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They-- they-- because, It was a strange feeling for me, because I knew those young people who were there and showing how they fought, they weren't the ones, because, after all, it was 50 years before.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it was unbelievable what they did-- used the same-- the same cars that we had.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They used the same bicycle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "At one point, there were 200 of them on bicycles, showing what happened when we had nothing else but bicycles to fight with.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was fabulous.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But you know, I think it's-- I don't know if this has already been said, but I said that there must be a record made of what happened to the French people during the war, what happened to the French Jews, and how they fought for their country-- and-- and how the patriots, and the first ones who joined the Resistance were the Jews.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mean, they didn't wait for the last 15 minutes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My husband was surrounded by Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And this had never been told enough.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It's not-- it's not published.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's not in the-- it's not in the-- in the encyclopedia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it must be said, because-- because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the way the French Jews fought for their country and fought the Germans was really something to-- to-- to be-- not to be forgotten.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't get that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
